cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DS 

The paper discusses the vulnerability of machine learning algorithms to adversarial attacks and proposes a defense mechanism using randomized smoothing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also involves theoretical and empirical analysis, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
